.TH NETPKG 8 "April 2026" "Netpkg 11.5" "System Administration Utilities"

.SH NAME
netpkg \- network package management tool for Zenwalk Linux

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B netpkg
.I command
.RI [ arguments ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B netpkg
is a command line package management utility designed for
Zenwalk Linux systems. It provides a simple interface for
installing, upgrading, removing, and searching software
packages from remote repositories over the network.

The tool allows minimal system installations and enables
administrators to install or update only the packages required
for a specific system.

.B netpkg
downloads package metadata from configured remote repositories,
compares them with installed packages, and performs the
necessary operations using the native Slackware package tools
such as
.BR installpkg (8)
and
.BR upgradepkg (8).

Dependency processing can optionally be enabled through the
configuration file.

.SH COMMANDS

.TP
.B update, -u
Synchronize the local package database with remote repositories.

.TP
.B upgrade, -U
Upgrade all installed packages for which newer versions exist
in the configured repositories.

.TP
.B update&upgrade, -uu
Perform both repository synchronization and system upgrade.

.TP
.B install, -i \fIpattern\fR
Search for packages matching the specified pattern and prompt
the user for installation.

Multiple search patterns may be specified.

.TP
.B remove, -r \fIpattern\fR
Search for installed packages matching the pattern and prompt
for removal.

.TP
.B search, -s \fIpattern\fR
Search remote and local package databases and display matching
packages.

.TP
.B remotes, -rl
List configured remote repositories.

.TP
.B remote-add, -ra \fIURL\fR
Add a new remote repository using the specified URL.

.TP
.B remote-disable, -rd
Disable an existing remote repository.

.TP
.B remote-enable, -re
Enable a previously disabled remote repository.

.TP
.B deps-enable, -ed
Enable dependency handling in the configuration file.

.TP
.B deps-disable, -dd
Disable dependency handling.

.TP
.B dotnew, -z
Scan the system for configuration files ending in
.B .new
and interactively prompt for merge or replacement.

.TP
.B mrclean, -mc
Clean the local package cache directory.

.TP
.B help, -h
Display usage information.

.SH OUTPUT STATUS

During searches and upgrades, packages are marked with the
following status indicators:

.TP
.B [I]
Installed package matches the remote version.

.TP
.B [U]
Remote version is newer than the installed package.

.TP
.B [D]
Remote version is older than the installed package.

.TP
.B [R]
Package exists in remote repository but is not installed locally.

.SH CONFIGURATION

Configuration is stored in:

.TP
.I /etc/netpkg.conf

Key options include:

.TP
.B Netpkg_dir
Directory used for internal netpkg data.

.TP
.B Remotes_dir
Directory containing remote repository definitions.

.TP
.B Local_repository
Directory used to cache downloaded packages.

.TP
.B Package_logs
Directory containing installed package metadata.

.TP
.B Handle_dependencies
Enable or disable dependency processing.

.TP
.B Keep_packages
Controls whether downloaded packages remain in the local cache.

.TP
.B Proxy_Socket
Proxy configuration for network access.

.SH REMOTE REPOSITORIES

Remote repositories are defined as individual files located in:

.TP
.I /etc/netpkg.d/

Each file must contain at least:

.TP
.B URL
Base URL of the repository.

Optional:

.TP
.B Black_list
Packages excluded from synchronization.

.SH FILES

.TP
.I /etc/netpkg.conf
Main configuration file.

.TP
.I /etc/netpkg.d/
Remote repository configuration directory.

.TP
.I /var/netpkg/
Local metadata database directory.

.TP
.I /var/packages/
Local package cache.

.TP
.I /var/log/packages/
Installed package records.

.TP
.I /var/log/netpkg.log
Operation log file.

.SH EXIT STATUS

.TP
.B 0
Operation completed successfully.

.TP
.B 1
An error occurred.

.SH EXAMPLES

Update repository metadata:

.nf
netpkg update
.fi

Upgrade the system:

.nf
netpkg upgrade
.fi

Install a package:

.nf
netpkg install vim
.fi

Search for packages:

.nf
netpkg search python
.fi

Add a repository:

.nf
netpkg remote-add http://mirror.example.org/zenwalk
.fi

